<HEADLINE>
FT  31 DEC 94 / Pay ranking blow for chief executives
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain's chief executives are paid less than most of their international
counterparts, says a survey by management consultants Towers Perrin.
British chief executive officers came 16th out of 19 countries surveyed in
terms of total cash remuneration (salary and bonuses) - one place higher
than in 1993. Their total pay amounted to Pounds 158,000 compared with
Pounds 311,000 received by their equivalents in the US, who topped the
league table.
</TEXT>
