<HEADLINE>
FT  31 DEC 94 / Polish draft budget passed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BOBINSKI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WARSAW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Sejm, the Polish parliament's lower chamber, yesterday passed the
country's 1995 draft budget by a large majority in the face of pay demands
by Solidarity-led health workers and teachers, which if successful could
destroy the government's monetary strategy. The draft foresees a deficit at
3.3 per cent of gross domestic product which has already been agreed with
the IMF but the budget has come under attack from President Lech Walesa, who
has backed the Solidarity pay demands.
</TEXT>
