FT  31 DEC 94 / Australia to harden refugee law
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Australia's federal government yesterday disclosed plans to toughen its laws
on 'refugee status', in an effort to stem the flow of boat people arriving
from southern China. About 950 boat people, predominantly Chinese, have
landed in northern Australia this year. Senator Nick Bolkus, federal
immigration minister, said the government planned to ensure that illegal
arrivals could not claim refugee status on the grounds of China's
restrictions on the number of children couples can have. He said that many
of the recent arrivals had cited this policy in claiming refugee status.
