<HEADLINE>
FT  30 DEC 94 / Immigrants worry Australians
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Australia's federal government is being urged to step up pressure on China
in an effort to halt a sudden influx of illegal refugees reaching Australia
by boat from the southern Chinese city of Beihai. On Wednesday, a vessel
with more than 70 people on board entered Darwin, the fourth in six days
believed to be from the Chinese port town. This brought the number of boat
people, predominantly Chinese, arriving in northern Australia this year to
about 950, the highest annual total since the Vietnam war. More than
two-thirds of the arrivals have occurred in the last six weeks.
</TEXT>
