FT  30 DEC 94 / Japanese quake kills three
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Balancing act: an elderly woman makes her way cautiously along an
earthquake-damaged road towards her daughter's house in the northern
Japanese city of Hachinohe yesterday. Aftershocks and snow squalls hampered
relief and repair efforts in the wake of Wednesday's tremor that killed
three people - two of them in Hachinohe - and injured 267.
